 vs. extracted_answer: Key diagnostic findings for this patient include a profound leukocytosis at admission (WBC 139.3 x 10^3/uL) and a peak LDH of 809 U/L. Cytogenetic studies identified the Philadelphia chromosome translocation t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) in 100% of cells (20/20). FISH analysis confirmed the BCR/ABL1 gene rearrangement in 95% of cells using the SpectrumOrange (ABL1) and SpectrumGreen (BCR) dual color dual fusion translocation probe set. Diagnostic imaging revealed splenomegaly (14.5 cm) via ultrasound and 17 cm of abnormal bone marrow edema/infiltration in the distal right femur on MRI, consistent with marrow CML infiltration. The patient's Eutos score was 67.7, indicating low-risk disease. By the time of discharge, the WBC count was recorded at 90.5 x 10^3/uL.; SCORE: 0.7875
