Discharge Condition: The patient was discharged in stable condition, ambulatory and steady. The surgical incision was clean, dry, and intact with steristrips. Residual neurological findings included trace left plantar flexion and dorsiflexion weakness with slight sensory loss to light touch over the lateral aspect of the left foot.; SCORE: 0.825
